OL,3,CEx-police officer convicted over death
OL,4,Cthreat 'lie' which led to man's arrest
OL,6,FJudge Sherrard said that whilst the
OL,7,Fmotivation for Moffitt's offending was
OL,8,F"unclear", it "seems likely" he was
OL,9,Ftrying to "either impress or gain
OL,10,Fsympathy from a female colleague."
OL,12,FCiting the offending as a "cry for
OL,13,Fhelp", Judge Sherrard said it occurred
OL,14,Fwhen Moffitt's mind was "warped with
OL,15,Falcohol."
OL,17,FJudge Sherrard told Moffitt that as he
OL,18,Fwas a police officer at the time, his
OL,19,Factions were "clearly in breach of the
OL,20,Fduty of trust placed in you by our
OL,21,Fcommunity."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/10
