OL,3,CEx-police officer convicted over death
OL,4,Cthreat 'lie' which led to man's arrest
OL,6,FTelling Moffitt his offending was "not
OL,7,Fsophisticated", the Judge added: "It
OL,8,Fis not lost upon me that you have not
OL,9,Fonly lost you job, but you have also
OL,10,Flost your reputation as a result of
OL,11,Fthis stupid error."
OL,13,FThe Judge also said that in the
OL,14,Fintervening four years, Moffitt's life
OL,15,Fhas moved from "chaos to order" and he
OL,16,Fhas not committed any further offences.
OL,18,FImposing the suspended sentence, Judge
OL,19,FSherrard warned Moffitt of the
OL,20,Fconsequences should be re-offend in
OL,21,Fthe next three years.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/10
